      "content": "The shame you feel is a heavy burden, but please remember that even the most successful entrepreneurs have faced failures that once seemed insurmountable. It is incredibly difficult to reconcile the public image you built with the harsh reality of the collapse, and that internal conflict is painful. However, the truth is often more powerful than a facade, and facing it head-on is the only way to truly move forward. You don't have to carry this alone; consider speaking with a therapist who specializes in financial trauma or a mentor who has walked a similar path. There are people who understand the weight of failure and can help you rebuild your identity beyond the business.",
